Everything the palette renders comes from tagged tiddlers. To add functionality, ship a tiddler with the right tag and the right `ca-*` fields. No JS needed for most contributions.

! Contribution tags

|!Tag suffix |!What you contribute |
|`/entry` |A root-level row — drill / fire / open |
|`/action` |An action menu item — appears when its `ca-entity-type` matches |
|`/leader` |A keyboard shortcut after `Ctrl-Space` |
|`/filter` |A Filter strip pill |
|`/visibility` |A Visibility strip pill |
|`/reach` |A Reach strip pill |
|`/field` |A Search-in strip pill |
|`/view` |An alternate view of the same data |
|`/preset` |A pre-shipped configuration snapshot |
|`/template` |A row-detail-drawer template (Ctrl-hold) |
|`/help` |A help section (you're reading the output) |
|`/diagnostic` |A diagnostic tile shown under Configurations → Diagnostics |
|`/setting` |A settings row shown under Configurations → Settings |

Each tag prefix is `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette` — e.g. the full tag for a help section is `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/help`.

! Help section schema (this surface)

|!Field |!Purpose |
|`ca-name` |Display name |
|`ca-icon` |Glyph |
|`ca-group` |Category for visual grouping. Use `Plugin: <slug>` to land in the Plugins drill. |
|`ca-order` |Sort order (lower first) |
|`ca-hint` |One-line subtitle |
|`text` |Wikitext body rendered in the side preview |

! Where to put your tiddler

* ''In a plugin'' — `$:/plugins/<author>/<plugin>/help/<slug>`. One tiddler per plugin is the convention.
* ''In a wiki'' — any title works; just tag it `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/help`.

''→'' Every field of every protocol: <$link to="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/protocol">doc/protocol</$link>
